Latest Articles






DealBook

                    Validus Abandons Transatlantic Bid                
The long fight for Transatlantic Holdings appears to be finally over.










DealBook

                    Alleghany to Buy Transatlantic for $3.4 Billion                
7:07 a.m. | Updated










DealBook

                    Another Potential Transatlantic Suitor Emerges                
Two bidders for Transatlantic Holdings have already walked away, but another potential suitor may yet make an offer for the reinsurance company.










DealBook

                    New Transatlantic Suitors Said to Include Former Treasury Official                
A former government official who helped bail out the American International Group and a onetime head of General Re are part of a group that has begun merger talks with Transatlantic Holdings, people briefed on the matter told DealBook on Tuesday.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic and Validus Sign a Confidentiality Agreement                
Transatlantic Holdings and Validus Holdings said on Friday that they had signed a confidentiality agreement, setting up negotiations that could lead to a merger of the two reinsurance companies.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic Says Berkshire Bid Remains $3.25 Billion                
Transatlantic Holdings said on Monday that Berkshire Hathaway's takeover bid for the reinsurer remains $3.25 billion in cash, ensuring that the two companies will not strike a deal.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic Ends Deal With Allied World                
Transatlantic Holdings and Allied World Assurance called off their proposed $2.94 billion merger on Friday, after the two insurers faced stiff shareholder opposition and two rival bids for Transatlantic.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic Suitors Wait for Allied Deal to Slip Away                
Time is running out on Transatlantic Holdings' attempt to merge with Allied World Assurance.










DealBook

                    Validus Seeks to Replace Transatlantic Board                
The reinsurer Validus Holdings said on Wednesday that it would seek to replace the board of Transatlantic Holdings.










DealBook

                    I.S.S. Comes Out Against Transatlantic's Deal With Allied                
The proposed merger of Transatlantic Holdings with Allied World Assurance experienced a fresh setback on Friday, as a major shareholder advisory firm recommended that investors vote against the $2.86 billion deal.














DealBook

                    Transatlantic Scores Small Win in Fight With Validus                
Transatlantic Holdings was dealt a big blow this week in its fight to fend off a hostile $2.9 billion bid by Validus Holdings, after a major investor publicly opposed its preferred merger with Allied World Assurance.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic's Biggest Investor Opposes Allied Deal                
Transatlantic Holdings's biggest shareholder, Davis Selected Advisors, said on Thursday that it opposed the insurer's proposed $2.9 billion merger with Allied World Assurance.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic and Berkshire Begin Talks                
The reinsurer Transatlantic says it has begun deal negotiations with a unit of Berkshire Hathaway, officially adding a third party to the takeover fray.










DealBook

                    Validus Sues Transatlantic Over Deal Hurdles                
Validus sued Transatlantic Holdings in a Delaware state court, hoping to force the reinsurer to begin deal negotiations after weeks of refusals.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic Seeks Talks With Berkshire Unit                
Transatlantic said that while the $3.25 billion bid by Berkshire Hathaway was not a “superior proposal” to an already agreed-upon merger with Allied World Assurance, it was likely to lead to one.










DealBook

                    Even Berkshire Falls Short in Deal Battles                
Berkshire Hathaway’s bid for Transatlantic Holdings is the highest offer on the table. But Warren Buffett’s deal machine has fallen short before.










DealBook

                    Berkshire Unit Bids $3.25 Billion for Transatlantic                
The $52-a-share bid by Berkshire’s National Indemnity tops competing offers from Validus Holdings and Allied World Assurance.










DealBook

                    Validus Chief on Transatlantic Bid: ‘We’re Not Going Away’                
The Validus chairman and chief executive, Edward Noonan, took issue with the board of Transatlantic Holdings for rebuffing his company’s takeover bid and vowed to stick around.










DealBook

                    Transatlantic Rejects Hostile Validus Bid and Files a Lawsuit                
Transatlantic rebuffed Validus, saying that the hostile bid was too low and that Transatlantic remained committed to its own planned merger with Allied World Assurance.


























