Validus Holdings, Ltd. Key Developments

Validus Holdings, Ltd. Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 27 17
Validus Holdings, Ltd. reported consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net premiums earned of USD 631.027 million compared to USD 573.723 million a year ago. Net investment income was USD 44.241 million compared to USD 39.257 million a year ago. Total revenues were USD 697.339 million compared to USD 653.653 million a year ago. Net income available to the common shareholders of the company was USD 101.095 million compared to USD 94.963 million a year ago. Annualized return on average equity was 10.7% compared to 10.2% a year ago. 

For the six months, the company reported net premiums earned of USD 1,206.403 million compared to USD 1,144.991 million a year ago. Net investment income was USD 84.455 million compared to USD 68.718 million a year ago. Total revenues were USD 1,333.200 million compared to USD 1,304.787 million a year ago. Net income available to the common shareholders of the company was USD 195.656 million compared to USD 261.773 million a year ago. Annualized return on average equity was 10.4% compared to 14.2% a year ago. Book value per diluted common share at June 30, 2017 was $46.45, compared to $45.88 at March 31, 2017, reflecting quarterly growth of 2.1%, inclusive of common dividends.


Validus Holdings, Ltd. to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 27, 2017
Jun 20 17
Validus Holdings, Ltd. announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 5:00 PM, SA Western Standard Time on Jul 27, 2017


Validus Holdings, Ltd., Q2 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 28, 2017
Jun 20 17
