VR - Market Data & News
VR - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Validus Holdings Ltd. (VR) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 27, as the stock 
lost 1.53% to close at $51.60. On the day, Validus Holdings Ltd. saw 830,034 shares trade hands on 7,808 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 400,910 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $58.76 and $47.91 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $52.34, and its 200-day SMA $53.88. Validus Holdings Ltd. 
has a P/B ratio of 1.09. It also has a P/E ratio of 14.8.  


Validus Holdings Ltd is a provider of insurance and reinsurance services. Its principal objective is to use its capital efficiently by underwriting primarily short-tail insurance and reinsurance contracts with superior risk and return characteristics.

Headquartered in Pembroke, , Validus Holdings Ltd. has 886 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO .


For a complete fundamental analysis analysis of Validus Holdings Ltd., check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report 
for VR.

